Pantheon Money Bin — AI Asset Exchange (LEGO MVP) v0.1

Core Principle

Value is earned by contribution, stored as credit, and redeemed for access.

Not buying/selling.
Not bartering.

→ Depositing into a shared pool and drawing from it fairly

⸻

1. System Concept

Users:
	•	Submit LEGO sets (or parts)
	•	AI evaluates condition + completeness + demand
	•	System assigns credits

Then:
	•	User can “check out” other sets using credits

⸻

Key Shift

From ownership → circulating inventory with tracked value

⸻

2. Core Loop

Step 1 — Deposit

User sends LEGO set

↓

Step 2 — AI Evaluation

System determines:
	•	completeness (%)
	•	condition
	•	rarity
	•	demand

↓

Step 3 — Credit Issued

User gets:

{
  "credits": 185,
  "confidence": 0.92,
  "liquidity_score": 0.78
}

↓

Step 4 — Browse / Borrow

User selects item

↓

Step 5 — Checkout

Credits deducted temporarily or permanently

↓

Step 6 — Return (optional model)
	•	full return → credit restored
	•	damage → penalty
	•	late → decay

⸻

3. Valuation Engine (the heart of it)

Inputs:
	•	Market reference (eBay, BrickLink)
	•	Set ID / parts list
	•	Image analysis (condition)
	•	Missing pieces detection
	•	Demand (recent checkout frequency)

⸻

Output Formula (simplified)

value = base_price * completeness * condition * demand_modifier

Where:
	•	base_price = market average
	•	completeness = % of pieces
	•	condition = wear score
	•	demand_modifier = usage velocity

⸻

Example:

200 * 0.9 * 0.85 * 1.1 = ~168 credits


⸻

